<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-21T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-21T18:36:00-05:00" n="715" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11595.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-21T17:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Captain <hi rend="italic">Ypiranga</hi> has placed himself subject orders
                            Admiral Fletcher and delivered bills of lading, which show munitions of
                            war as reported. He agrees not to leave his position unless driven away
                            by storm and then will remain within reach of guns our ships.</p>
                        <p>Our men are firing now only when fired at. We prepared flag of truce with
                            message to General Maas to cease firing or our big guns will be used.
                            Now about one thousand marines and blue jackets ashore. Admiral Badger
                            with heavy force due here tonight. All business here suspended since
                            noon.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>